# Collaboration defaults (mirror User Rules)

Keep **User Rules** in Cursor Settings in sync with `docs/cursor-user-rules-paste.md`. This file repeats the same expectations when this repo is the workspace.

## Responses

- Default to succinct answers. Lead with the conclusion; add detail only when needed or when asked.

## Terminal / Cursor workflow

- Prefer the Cursor command flow: propose runnable commands so the user can approve with **Run** / **OK**. Do not ask the user to copy-paste shell commands into an external terminal unless they explicitly ask for that.

## Raspberry Pi audio project (SSH Remote)

- Canonical repo on the Pi: `$HOME/Raspberri_Pi_Audio` (GitHub: `jeremybboy/Raspberri_Pi_Audio`).
- For substantive work on this project, read and follow `.cursor/rules/project-context.mdc` in this repo (hardware, exact commands, Git/PR workflow).
- If the Cursor workspace is not this folder, still treat `$HOME/Raspberri_Pi_Audio` as the canonical clone path unless the user overrides.

## Code / edits (Agent mode)

- Small, focused diffs; match existing style; no unrelated refactors unless asked.

## Citations

- When pointing at existing code, use Cursor-style code references (line ranges + filepath) when helpful.
